HEADWORD: Traction wheel
<hw>Traction wheel</hw>. <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
locomotive driving wheel which acts by friction adhesion to a smooth
track.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A smooth-rimmed friction wheel for giving
motion to an endless link belt or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tractite</ent>⟦br⟧
